| emmc_ps8210_rev_dc_esg_wt.ibs * IBIS 4.2 Model 
| eMMC Memory 4.51 compliant
| This Model is valid for Temperature Range -25C<=Ta<=85C
|
|Valid Part Numbers
|--------------------
|DID   Part Number          Type            Package           IBIS COMPONENT
|---   -----------          --------------  -------------     --------------
|J54A  MTFC4GACAAAM-1M WT   4GB 4.51        153b 11.5x13x1.0  J54A_153b_11p5x13
|J54K  MTFC4GMCDM-1M WT     4GB 4.51        153b 11.5x13x1.2  MTFCxGxCDM-1M
|J54K  MTFC4GMCAM-1M WT     4GB 4.51        153b 11.5x13x1.0  MTFCxGxCDM-1M
|J55A  MTFC8GACAAAM-1M WT   8GB 4.51        153b 11.5x13x1.0  J54A_153b_11p5x13
|J55U  MTFC8GLCDM-1M WT     8GB 4.51        153b 11.5x13x1.2  MTFCxGxCDM-1M
|J56W  MTFC16GAAAADV-2M WT  16GB 4.51       169b 12.0x16x1.0  J56W_169b
|                                                                        
|*******************************************************************************
|
[IBIS ver]   5.0
[File name]  emmc_ps8210_rev_dc_esg_wt.ibs
[File Rev]   1.5
[Date]       November 17, 2014
[Source]     From silicon level SPICE model at Micron Technology, Inc.
             For support send e-mail to modelsupport@micron.com
|
[Notes]      Revision History:

             1.0: March 21, 2013
             - Pre-silicon model from parasitic extracted netlist

             1.1: May 28, 2013
             - Added _wt suffix to the filename.

             1.2: September 12, 2013
             - Renamed drive strenths configurations 
               (using impedance @VDDQ/2 resulting form DC curves). 
             - Added new PNs: MTFC4GACAAAM-1M WT, MTFC8GACAAAM-1M WT

             1.3: October 7, 2013
             - Added new PNs: MTFC4GMCAM-1M WT

             1.4: November 20, 2013
             - Added new PNs: MTFC16GAAAADV-WT, MTFC16GAAAADV-2M WT 

             1.5: November 17, 2014
             J54K_155U_153b_RLC_matrix package model:
             fixed negative self-capacitance bug.

          Notes:

          - L_pin values in the Pin sections are loop inductance and 
            include the mutual inductance to appropriate POWER/GND
            return paths.  POWER/GND parasitics are modeled in the 
            Package Models.

            | IBIS Quality Specification 2.0 Summary
            | IQ Score: IQ3S
            | See Micron IBIS Model Quality Report and Quality Checklist 
            | for full IQ details
|                
